Production pattern для stateful KeyedProcessFunction в Python: ```python
class FraudDetector(KeyedProcessFunction):
    def open(self, runtime_context):
        descriptor = ValueStateDescriptor('last_tx', Types.DOUBLE())
        self.last_amount = runtime_context.get_state(descriptor)
        # Также get_list_state, get_map_state
        # Metrics через runtime_context.get_metric_group()

    def process_element(self, value, ctx):
        user_id, amount = value
        last = self.last_amount.value()  # None if empty
        if last and amount > last * 10:
            yield {'alert': 'fraud', 'user': user_id}
        self.last_amount.update(amount)
        # Register timer
        ctx.timer_service().register_event_time_timer(ctx.timestamp() + 60_000)

    def on_timer(self, timestamp, ctx):
        # Called when timer fires
        yield f'timer at {timestamp}'```. Use: `stream.key_by(lambda e: e[0], key_type=Types.INT()).process(FraudDetector(), output_type=Types.MAP(STRING(), STRING()))`. **Three state types**: ValueState (single value), ListState (append/get/update list), MapState (key→value pairs). All serialized through TypeInformation declared в descriptor. State persists across checkpoints — full restoration. **Timer types**: event_time (fires when watermark passes), processing_time (wall clock). Timer state automatically checkpointed.
